# Trivy suppressions for the worker image scan (.github/workflows/ci.yaml).
# Each entry documents a vulnerability we have evaluated and accepted; the
# bare CVE id on its own line is what actively suppresses it. Review on each
# worker-image bump and delete entries whose fix has shipped.

# CVE-2026-33671 - npm-bundled tinyglobby/picomatch 4.0.3 ReDoS (4.0.4 fixes);
# only npm's transitive, single-tenant worker, unreachable from a prompt attacker.
CVE-2026-33671

# CVE-2026-34040 - Docker SDK Moby daemon authz-bypass (v29.3.1 fixes);
# the chat service uses the Docker *client* only, against a trusted local
# daemon; govulncheck reports no finding. v28->v29 major bump pending
# Dependabot review.
CVE-2026-34040

# --- The apt-installed GitHub CLI (/usr/bin/gh, latest release v2.96.0) is a
# prebuilt upstream binary compiled with Go 1.26.4; CVE-2026-39822 is an
# os.Root symlink-following traversal in that embedded stdlib, fixed in Go
# 1.26.5. Everything this repo compiles is already on 1.26.5 (builder image,
# in-image toolchain, agent binary - all scan clean); only GitHub's release
# pipeline can rebuild gh. Inside the worker container repo-controlled code
# already executes arbitrary bash, so gh's traversal adds no marginal attack
# surface. Clears when apt pulls a gh release built on Go >= 1.26.5.
CVE-2026-39822

# CVE-2026-48815 - npm-bundled sigstore 4.1.0: certificateOIDs verification
# constraints are silently dropped and never enforced (4.1.1 fixes). npm CLI's
# own transitive dependency, exercised only when npm verifies registry
# attestations inside the single-tenant worker; clears when a base-image npm
# upgrade ships the fixed sigstore.
CVE-2026-48815
